The original square has side length \(s\) and area \(s^2\). After decreasing two opposite sides by \(40\%\), their lengths become \(0.6s\). The other two sides are increased by \(50\%\), so their lengths become \(1.5s\). The rectangle formed has dimensions \(0.6s\) by \(1.5s\), giving an area of \(0.6s \times 1.5s = 0.9s^2\).

The area decreases by \(s^2 - 0.9s^2 = 0.1s^2\). As a percentage of the original area, this is \(\frac{0.1s^2}{s^2} \times 100\% = 10\%\).

\boxed{10\%}

